<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="43" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, BP" journalOrPublisher="Aquatic Insects" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="45 - 50" title="Records and descriptions of Oriental Neoperlini (Plecoptera: Perlidae)." url="10.1080/01650428709361270" volume="9" year="1987">Stark (1987)</bibRefCitation>
from Vietnam and China based on three males (two from Vietnam, one from China), its female was recently associated (
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, BP" journalOrPublisher="Illiesia" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="19 - 54" title="New species and records of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Vietnam." volume="4" year="2008">Stark and Sivec 2008</bibRefCitation>
). One male was available to the present study and the tip of sac seems slightly hooked with sharper apex that appears somewhat blunt in original drawing (fig. 6 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, BP" journalOrPublisher="Aquatic Insects" pageId="8" pageNumber="45" pagination="45 - 50" title="Records and descriptions of Oriental Neoperlini (Plecoptera: Perlidae)." url="10.1080/01650428709361270" volume="9" year="1987">Stark 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
